
------------- Ubuntu(Linux) -----------
Button Index = Button
0 = A
1 = B
2 = X
3 = Y

4 = Left Button
5 = Right Button

6 = Back
7 = Start
8 = Xbox button

9 = Left joystick
10 = Right joystick

Axis = Button

R = Right Trigger
Z = Left Trigger

X = Left Joystick (X wise)
Y = Left Joystick (Y wise)

U = Right Joystick (X wise)
V = Right Joystick (Y wise)

PovX = Keypad (X wise)
PovY = Keypad (Y wise)

------------- Windows(Windows 7) -----------
Button Index = Button
0 = A
1 = B
2 = X
3 = Y

4 = Left Button
5 = Right Button

6 = Back
7 = Start

8 = Left Joystick
9 = Right joystick

Axis = Button

R = Right Joystick(Y wise)
U = Right Joystick (X wise)

Z = Both triggers (~(100) is Right trigger, ~(-100) is Left trigger)

X = Left Joystick (X wise)
Y = Left Joystick (Y wise)

V = Nothing? (Locked at -100)

PovX = Keypad (Y wise)
PovY = Keypad (X wise)